{
  "text": "The sustained increase in serum NF-H levels, especially in the light of the similarly elevated MBP levels, indicates ongoing white matter damage. White matter injury detected by diffusion-tensor imaging (DTI) has been identified as a hallmark of mTBI [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Indeed, in our current study as well as previous experiments, we have found indications of myelin damage reflected by elevated serum MBP levels [CITATION_4] . Both experimental and clinical imaging studies have found white matter tract damages following blast exposure(s) [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . The exact pathology that can cause and or sustain long-term axonal damage is currently not fully understood, but inflammatory responses have been implicated in the long-term effect of bTBI [CITATION_8] .",
  "correct_citation": {
